\nw[Grand]First, let me introduce myself. I am Grand. I am
the leader of this group.

\nw[Grand]After that, it's Rouge, Gerold, and Amy from the
top.
\nw[Taro]Ah, I am...
\nw[Grand]It's Taro, you know. So relax.
\nw[Taro]I see.

\nw[Taro](They're suspicious characters, and I don't even
know their real names...)

\nw[Grand]We are members of the Dios Army. We pretend to be
adventurers and gather information about this
country.
\nw[Taro]Dios...

\nw[Grand]Ah, it's probably your hometown as well. That's
why I called out to you.
\nw[Taro]So you're still investigating me, huh...

\nw[Taro]No, I don't care about that. What's more important
is how to meet the witch. Will you tell me?
\nw[Grand]Ah, if you join our plan, you can meet her.
\nw[Taro]So, what is that plan?

\nw[Grand]This time's plan is to attack the two Aegis. One
of them is No.II, Conductor.
\nw[Grand]And the other one is No.IX, Eater.
\nw[Taro]What... This is clearly a crime!

\nw[Grand]We are only conducting operations against the
virtual enemy country, Misura. And, we have had
important people taken away by the Eater.
\nw[Grand]It's also revenge.

\nw[Taro](Certainly, I haven't completely lost my desire
for revenge... but there's no way I can defeat the
Eater... I don't want to die in vain, to begin
with.)

\nw[Taro]What does that have to do with meeting the witch?!
It's completely unrelated!

\nw[Grand]The command system of the strongest ten members of
the Misura country, the Aegis, is under the orders
of the <Conductor>.

\nw[Grand]In other words, the <Conductor> has the authority
to give orders to the <Witch>. If we can charm the
<Conductor>, we may be able to give orders to the
<Witch> and even meet her.

\nw[Grand]We should be able to not only meet her, but also
give orders.
\nw[Taro]Hmmm.

\nw[Grand]As Dios, it is convenient for us to have control
over the top of the information department. That's
why we need your power.
\nw[Taro]......The power of a succubus, huh.

\nw[Grand]That's right. I called you here to charm the
<Conductor> with the power of a succubus.
\nw[Taro]I see...

\nw[Taro](My succubus ability is that of an NTR succubus.
Depending on the partner, it may not be very
effective...)

\nw[Taro](If they think I'm useless, it could be dangerous
for me... Maybe I should just stay quiet...)

\nw[Grand]Lately, I've been observing the movements of the
<Conductor>, but they don't have much power
themselves.

\nw[Grand]They can use Dollmaster magic, but compared to
other Aegis, they're just small fry. It means
they're an opponent I can easily defeat on my own.

\nw[Taro]Quite the confidence you have. In the first place,
there's no way I can fight against such a powerful
person from the military on my own. And if there
are two of them, that means there's also someone
to devour, right?

\nw[Taro]Are you saying I can defeat them too? The monster
who single-handedly defeated thousands of Dios
soldiers.

\nw[Grand]They are strong. That much is obvious. That's why
we gathered information in order to defeat them in
Dios.

\nw[Grand]What we learned from those results is... that
person...
\nw[Taro]...Is it true?

\nw[Grand]It's not that I personally investigated, but
that's what the research team in Dios is saying.
\nw[Taro]...I see...

\nw[Grand]Now that you've heard the whole story, you don't
have the right to refuse. I won't let you escape
until you become an accomplice.

\nw[Taro]I understand. But what are we going to do about
the attack?

\nw[Grand]I know the location of the <Dollmaster> tonight.
There is also <someone to devour> with them.

\nw[Grand]They are currently without any significant troops.
That's why tonight is the perfect opportunity for
an attack.
\nw[Taro]I understand.

\nw[Grand]Alright, please get ready. We will depart as soon
as the preparations are complete.
\nw[Taro]Ah, I understand.

\nw[Taro](It really is a dangerous story... If I try to
escape, I feel like they'll kill me to keep me
quiet...)

\nw[Taro](Even if I manage to escape, I'm sure the country
of Dios itself will start to antagonize me. And
this problem won't just affect me, but also the
mercenary group.)

\nw[Taro](If that happens, Kuno, Nonna... everyone else
will be in danger too...)
\nw[Taro](Was it already a mistake when I came here...?)

\nw[Taro](No, there is a way for me to continue living as
usual... and also to help Prae)

\nw[Taro](If we can successfully carry out this attack and
captivate the <Dollmaster>, they won't become
hostile either.)
\nw[Taro](Damn it... There's no choice but to do it...!)
\nw[Grand]Are you ready? If you're ready, then let's depart.
Ready

\nw[Grand]Alright. Then let's go.

\nw[Grand]Then prepare yourself.

\nw[Grand]He is strong. That much is obvious. That's why we
gathered information to defeat him in Dios.

\nw[Grand]As a result, we have learned something. His magic
can only be used in specific situations.
\nw[Taro]What do you mean?

\nw[Amy]Since analyzing magic is my specialty, I will
explain.

\nw[Amy]Dios, who felt threatened by the <threatening
entity>, gathered data about the battlefield where
the <threatening entity> fought. As a result, we
have learned one thing.
\nw[Taro]What did you understand?

\nw[Amy]When the <threatening entity> appears, our forces
are usually in a state of near annihilation or
close to it, and we are being pursued by the enemy
forces.

\nw[Amy]And then, it descends in front of the pursuing
enemy forces, rampages around, and after a while,
it suddenly disappears.

\nw[Taro]Hmmm... What does that have to do with anything?
It doesn't seem relevant to defeating him...

\nw[Amy]In other words, we speculated that it is a magic
that can only be used in that situation. If it can
be used, it would be more effective to deploy it
to the front lines from the beginning.
\nw[Taro]That's certainly true, but...

\nw[Amy]The ability of the <threatening entity> is simple.
It involves enhancing the body through magic and
neutralizing magic through its roar.

\nw[Amy]If those two things are true, then there would be
no problem if it were underground. That's why I
actually observed and analyzed its abilities.
\nw[Taro](So it was buried...)

\nw[Amy]First is the physical enhancement, but this was
not ordinary.

\nw[Amy]It was a creature that, despite constantly tearing
its muscles, crushing its bones, and bursting its
blood vessels due to excessive enhancement,
appeared to have a normal body at first glance,
thanks to its enhanced regenerative abilities.

\nw[Amy]It goes without saying, but an unimaginable
intense pain runs through you. If it were a normal
person, they would faint instantly.
\nw[Taro]Oh... That's terrible.

\nw[Amy]Therefore, the <threatening entity> shouldn't have
any consciousness during battle. However, the fact
that it still moves means that it must be moving
automatically through magic.

\nw[Amy]And it cannot distinguish between friend and foe.
That's why the <threatening entity> only appears
when our forces are in a state of complete
destruction.

\nw[Amy]And this is about another magic that the
<threatening entity> uses, called Roar.

\nw[Amy]It was difficult to analyze because it neutralizes
magic, but the mechanism is actually quite simple.

\nw[Amy]Simply put, it's just releasing an enormous amount
of magical power with its roar. With each roar, it
carries more than ten times the total amount of
magical power of an average magician.
\nw[Taro]Huh? And that's how it can neutralize magic?

\nw[Amy]The difference in magical power is so great that
it appears to be nullifying, but it's simply
crushing it with sheer force.

\nw[Amy]And then, the voice is so loud that it inevitably
disrupts concentration... or rather, if you're too
close, it momentarily paralyzes your body, causing
your incantations and such to be canceled.
\nw[Taro]So both of them are just brute force, huh?

\nw[Amy]That's right. However, there is something that we
have learned from these results.

\nw[Amy]The <threatening entity> has an abnormally intense
magic consumption. Even with physical enhancement,
it uses unnecessary magic by breaking and
regenerating, and as for its roar, it releases an
unimaginable amount of magic power.

\nw[Amy]No matter how skilled a magician is, if they keep
doing that, their magical power will run out in an
instant. If that's the case, there should be a way
to replenish magical power.
\nw[Taro]Hmmm, that's certainly true.

\nw[Amy]And as a result of creating and analyzing various
battlefields, we have discovered one fact.

\nw[Amy]The <threatening entity> consumes the magical
power of the deceased. And it continues to move
using that magical power.
\nw[Taro]......! The magical power of the deceased...?

\nw[Amy]That's right. Even if you die, your magical power
doesn't suddenly disappear.

\nw[Amy]So, in other words, by continuing to kill, the
<threatening entity> can replenish its energy.
That's why it is able to handle a large amount of
magical power.

\nw[Amy]1. There must be a large number of deceased
individuals with enough magical power to use
magic. 2. There must be no nearby allies to
provide support. 3. There must be a large number
of enemies, allowing for easy replenishment of
magical power.
\nw[Taro]......

\nw[Amy]We are few in number. And if we proceed without
killing soldiers as much as possible, the
<threatening entity> will not meet the conditions
to use magic.

\nw[Amy]The magic of the <threatening entity> is similar
to transformation. I believe that the <threatening
entity> that doesn't use magic looks completely
different in appearance.

\nw[Amy]After observing battles with the <threatening
entity>, we have found that it doesn't try to
defeat strong opponents. It simply aims to kill a
large number of weak opponents.

\nw[Amy]In reality, the majority of soldiers killed by the
<threatening entity> are not that strong. In fact,
if they were top-class soldiers of the country, as
long as they focus on defense, they would hardly
be killed.

\nw[Amy]However, the power, speed, and endurance are on a
completely different level, so we cannot protect
or hinder it.

\nw[Amy]The majority of soldiers killed by the
<threatening entity> were those who tried to
protect their allies or tried to restrain it,
resulting in futile efforts.

\nw[Taro](He said... If we die now, it would only be the
conductor, and I don't think the devourer would be

\nw[Taro]Speaking of which, how did you gather information

\nw[Grand]It seems like they've been manipulating various

\nw[Grand]I heard that they lured the <threatening entity>
by deceiving mercenaries and adventurers, making
them believe that they were attacking the thieves
instead of the soldiers from Misura, when the
Misura soldiers came to exterminate that bandit
group.
\nw[Taro]Wha... What...?

\nw[Grand]If they're not regular soldiers, they must think
it's okay to use them as disposable. Even
mercenaries can be a valuable fighting force. It
made me feel unpleasant when I heard about it
later.

\nw[Taro](The bandit extermination near the border... Could
it be the job when Kuno and Nonna were killed...?)
\nw[Taro](Dios... leading us to our deaths...?)
\nw[Grand]Alright, we're almost there. Be quiet.
\nw[Taro]......

\nw[Taro](There's no point in thinking about it now. I'll
have to confront them after this is over... I need
to switch gears...)
